{"id": 223690186, "title": "Government strict about new variant of Covid, order issued for random sample survey", "text": "New Delhi. Once again, the effect of Covid-19 has been seen in some states of India. According to the information, about three hundred and twenty five cases of KP 1 and KP 2 have been reported. After this, the government has issued strict orders and said that random samples should be taken from any place. The World Health Organization has expressed concern over the new form of Covid whose cases have been reported in different countries of the world including Singapore. On this basis, the Union Health Ministry has issued several important guidelines and orders in an important meeting held on Saturday after such cases were found in the country. At present, a survey will be conducted by taking random samples in different states of the country for a week. However, officials and experts associated with the Union Health Ministry say that this changed form of Covid is neither dangerous nor a matter of concern. At present, further strategy will be made on the basis of the report of the random sample survey in the second week of June. According to officials associated with the Union Health Ministry, so far about 290 cases of KP.2 have been reported in the country. Which includes 148 cases from Maharashtra. 36 cases have been found in West Bengal, 21 in Rajasthan, 23 in Gujarat, 16 in Uttarakhand, 12 in Goa, 17 in Odisha, 8 in Uttar Pradesh and 4 in Karnataka, including 3 in Haryana, 1 each in Madhya Pradesh and Delhi. To keep an eye on the cases of new variants and sub-variants in different states of the country, the Union Health Ministry has instructed for random sample survey.", "summary": "<p>New Delhi. Once again, the effect of Covid-19 has been seen in some states of India. According to the information, about three hundred and twenty five cases of KP 1 and KP 2 have been reported. After this, the government has issued strict orders and said that random samples should be taken from any place. [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://thenewsglory.com/government-strict-about-new-variant-of-covid-order-issued-for-random-sample-survey/\">Government strict about new variant of Covid, order issued for random sample survey</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://thenewsglory.com\">The News Glory</a>.</p>", "url": "https://thenewsglory.com/government-strict-about-new-variant-of-covid-order-issued-for-random-sample-survey/", "image": "https://nextindiatimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/3h6oc989.png", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 13:05:39", "author": "The News Glory", "authors": ["The News Glory"], "language": "en", "source_country": "in", "sentiment": -0.743}